---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Home"
  description="A non-physicist and an AI walked to the frontier of quantum gravity. They started on April 23, 2026 with F = ma. They finished on May 11 with a paper headed for arXiv."
>
  <div class="page">
    <a href="#main" class="skip">Skip to content</a>

    <!-- Masthead -->
    <header class="masthead" role="banner">
      <div class="masthead-corners"></div>
      <p class="masthead-strap">An Independent Scientific Publication</p>
      <div class="masthead-line"><div class="masthead-line-rule"></div></div>
      <h1 class="masthead-title">
        <span class="masthead-title-main">Donkey</span>
        <span class="masthead-title-conn">on the</span>
        <span class="masthead-title-main">Edge</span>
      </h1>
      <div class="masthead-line"><div class="masthead-line-rule"></div></div>
      <p class="masthead-meta">
        <span class="dot">Vol. I, No. I</span>
        <span class="dot">May 2026</span>
        <span class="dot">donkeyontheedge.com</span>
      </p>
    </header>

    <main id="main">
      <!-- Frontispiece / Hero -->
      <section class="frontispiece" aria-label="Hero">
        <div class="plate">
          <div class="plate-inner">
            <img
              src="/images/donkeyedge.png"
              alt="A donkey stands at the edge of a cliff, looking out."
              width="800"
              height="600"
            />
          </div>
          <p class="plate-caption">
            <em>The edge. May 11, 2026.</em>
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Intro / Lede -->
      <section class="intro" aria-label="Introduction">
        <h2 class="intro-head">A non-physicist and an AI walked to the frontier of quantum gravity.</h2>
        <div class="intro-body">
          <p>They started on April&nbsp;23, 2026 with <em>F</em>&nbsp;=&nbsp;<em>ma</em>. They finished on May&nbsp;11 with a paper headed for arXiv. The full record of how it happened is here.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="intro-after">
          <div class="intro-after-rule"><div class="intro-after-mark"></div></div>
          <nav class="intro-nav" aria-label="Primary actions">
            <a href="/paper" class="btn-primary">Read the paper</a>
            <a href="/field-notes/a-little-help-for-my-friends" class="btn-secondary">Start with the symphony</a>
          </nav>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Story strip -->
      <section class="dispatches" aria-label="Timeline">
        <div class="dispatches-frame">
          <div class="dispatches-corner dispatches-corner-left"><span class="dispatches-corner-text">Timeline</span></div>
          <div class="dispatches-corner dispatches-corner-right"></div>
          <div class="dispatches-head">The record, in sequence</div>
          <div class="dispatches-rule"><div class="dispatches-rule-line"></div><div class="dispatches-rule-mark"></div></div>
          <div class="dispatches-body">
            <p><strong>April&nbsp;23, 2026.</strong> A man in Bend, Oregon asks Claude where to start learning quantum mechanics.</p>
            <p><strong>April&nbsp;23 to May&nbsp;10.</strong> Forty reference documents. Physics&nbsp;101 through the speculative frontier of quantum gravity.</p>
            <p><strong>May&nbsp;10.</strong> The open-problems survey points at a tractable question at the edge of the field. The research begins.</p>
            <p><strong>May&nbsp;11.</strong> Paper headed for arXiv.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="dispatches-foot">
            <span class="pulse" aria-hidden="true"></span>
            <span>The research continues. Paper&nbsp;2 in progress.</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Pull quote -->
      <blockquote class="pull-quote">
        <p class="pull-quote-text">"It is not that the universe has one answer for how much two observers can disagree. It has a hierarchy of answers, indexed by how structured the thing they are looking at is. And we can actually compute the hierarchy."</p>
        <footer><cite><a href="/field-notes/a-little-help-for-my-friends">A Little Help for My Friends</a></cite></footer>
      </blockquote>

      <!-- Table of contents -->
      <nav class="contents" aria-label="Site sections">
        <div class="contents-head">
          <h2 class="contents-head-title">Contents</h2>
          <p class="contents-head-sub">Vol. I, No. I</p>
        </div>

        <a href="/paper" class="toc-entry">
          <span class="toc-num">I</span>
          <div class="toc-body">
            <span class="toc-title">The Paper</span>
            <span class="toc-sub">Complexity-Sensitive Complementarity in Non-Isometric Holographic Codes</span>
            <span class="toc-desc">Two new theorems. Five results. The research, complete.</span>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a href="/curriculum" class="toc-entry">
          <span class="toc-num">II</span>
          <div class="toc-body">
            <span class="toc-title">The Curriculum</span>
            <span class="toc-sub">Physics&nbsp;101 to quantum gravity, 38 stations</span>
            <span class="toc-desc">The full learning path, visualized as a Victorian subway map.</span>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a href="/field-notes" class="toc-entry">
          <span class="toc-num">III</span>
          <div class="toc-body">
            <span class="toc-title">Field Notes</span>
            <span class="toc-sub">38 class reports, 10 research phase posts, 8 essays</span>
            <span class="toc-desc">The record of the work, written as it happened.</span>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a href="/method" class="toc-entry">
          <span class="toc-num">IV</span>
          <div class="toc-body">
            <span class="toc-title">The Method</span>
            <span class="toc-sub">What we did and what we are claiming</span>
            <span class="toc-desc">Six essays on the protocol, failure modes, and calibration.</span>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a href="/lab" class="toc-entry">
          <span class="toc-num">V</span>
          <div class="toc-body">
            <span class="toc-title">The Lab</span>
            <span class="toc-sub">Paper 2 in progress</span>
            <span class="toc-desc">What is happening right now. Updated as it happens.</span>
          </div>
        </a>
      </nav>
    </main>

    <!-- Colophon / Footer -->
    <footer class="colophon" role="contentinfo">
      <div class="colophon-mark">
        <div class="colophon-inner">
          <div class="colophon-portrait">
            <img src="/images/donkeyportrait.png" alt="" aria-hidden="true" width="80" height="80" />
          </div>
          <div class="colophon-byline">
            <span class="colophon-role">Adam Cagle</span>
            <span class="colophon-with">with</span>
            <span class="colophon-role">Claude (Anthropic), computational collaborator</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="colophon-rule">
        <div class="colophon-rule-line"></div>
        <div class="colophon-rule-mark"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="colophon-notes">
        <nav class="colophon-links" aria-label="Footer navigation">
          <a href="/paper">The Paper</a>
          <a href="/curriculum">The Curriculum</a>
          <a href="/field-notes">Field Notes</a>
          <a href="/method">The Method</a>
          <a href="/lab">The Lab</a>
          <a href="/about">About</a>
        </nav>
        <p class="colophon-meta">This site is run by Adam Cagle (the donkey). Built with Claude (Anthropic), computational collaborator. No tracking or analytics.</p>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </div>
</Base>
